daily_routine: Maria would wake at 5 AM to check the oyamel fir groves where monarchs
  traditionally clustered, marking butterfly densities in a hand-sewn notebook her
  grandmother had started in 1987. She'd guide small groups of visitors along the
  ancient paths, sharing stories in Purépecha about how her great-grandmother could
  predict butterfly arrival by the angle of morning shadows on sacred stones.
